item.title: [WFLY-5374] Server start-up fails on IBM JDK 1.8 (64-bit) on RHEL 6/7 in full/full-ha profile
item.description:

item.summary: Server start-up fails on IBM JDK 1.8 (64-bit) on RHEL 6/7 in full/full-ha profile

status.description: A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.

comments.comment: I tried to remove messaging-activemq subsystem and server started without error. Upgrade of ActiveMQ Artemis causes this regression.

This looks related to messaging and aritmetis loading native libs.
I cannot reproduce this locally, can you post core dump file
it should be this one: /tmp/dr10/jboss-eap-7.0/bin/javacore.20150921.051514.4815.0002.txt
Thanks Tomaz for looking at it. I've attached javacore.20150921.051514.4815.0002.txt. Let me know if JIT/System dump as needed.

I can not reproduce it locally but I suspect the error comes from the native libs from our artemis 1.1.0-wildfly-6 branch.
Could you confirm it starts fine when the journal-type is set to NIO instead?
You're right. Server starts without problem with journal-type set to NIO. Start with ASYNCIO (which is default) always fails.
WildFly 10CR2 uses the vanilla Artemis 1.1.0. The error is still happening with it so it looks like there is a real issue with its native lib on IBM JDK 8.
Assigning Back to Jeff so he can backport the fix to a fork or something
